data.text:
Vorres, Ian

New York: Charles Scribner's Sons, 1965. Hardcover. Red cloth/boards with gold lettering. Red, color-illutrated. dj with yellow lettering. xix, (5) 264 pp. with numerous bw photos. Good+/Good+ (light age toning to some pages, light shelf wear to boards, dust jacket has wear and small tears. Pages are otherwise clean and clear). Item #146950

The biography of Olga Alexandrovna, sister of Tsar Nicholas II of Russia. It covers her entire life span, from birth in Russia to her escape to Denmark in 1979, exile and new life in Canada and eventual death in Toronto. Several newspaper articles related are included tucked inside the book.

OCLC: 44620707
